Check Users at users and groups - Check admins at groups -> sudo
Check Given passwords for admission for if they are too weak like root, if so go to users and groups and click change password the generated new password.
Update system bottom of panel click ! 
Search Firewall and enable it
Check Passwords, type: sudo nano /etc/login.defs - edit values to : 
PASS_MAX_DAYS   90     # max password age (shorter is stricter)
PASS_MIN_DAYS   7      # min days before password can be changed
PASS_WARN_AGE   7     # days before warning user of expiry
Save crtl+O press enter then crtl+X
Check passwd complexity type: sudo nano /etc/pam.d/common-password.
Find: password        requisite                       pam_pwquality.so retry=3
Add: pam_pwquality.so retry=3 minlen=12 difok=3 ucredit=-1 lcredit=-1 dcredit=-1 ocredit=-1
Allow update manager to automatically update in automation section of update manager.
For forensic questions delete material after if itâ€™s not supposed to be on the computer.
If it asks to install a service google the latest version and type sudo apt update, than sudo apt install -y {service_name}
Check Readme for specific apps to keep uninstall all other applications. To remove apps run the purge command example: sudo apt purge -y ophcrack* wireshark*
Disable root login for SSH, install gedit: sudo apt install -y gedit, edit it: gedit admin:///etc/ssh/sshd_config, change permitlogin Yes to NO
